The main picture looks more like a bungalow or mansion. I was imagining cosy cottages with a small farm or yard outside. Also, you mention only a few countries, but I'm really interested in the markets that experienced near banking failures that led to supposedly a lot of small homes and cottages going for almost nothing thanks to a lot of bankrupt people.  Not that I want to take advantage but that seems to be the only way I could afford to move forever in a remote European village/cottage. When do you have a product to actually start viewing?
